Package: kmod-wireguard
Version: 6.6.51-r1
Depends: kernel (=6.6.51~9cb702c4f477bf85fe1f2bd037b7b8f1-r1), kmod-crypto-lib-chacha20poly1305, kmod-crypto-lib-curve25519, kmod-udptunnel4, kmod-udptunnel6
Source: feeds/base/kernel/linux
SourceName: kernel
License: GPL-2.0-only
LicenseFiles: COPYING
Section: kernel
SourceDateEpoch: 1725125284
Architecture: aarch64_cortex-a53
Installed-Size: 122880
Filename: kmod-wireguard_6.6.51-r1_aarch64_cortex-a53.ipk
Size: 42564
SHA256sum: 5008120fa560fdc8fca5ac3fbb1309a570723f97da3655605c990980f4820f9b
Description:  WireGuard is a novel VPN that runs inside the Linux Kernel and utilizes
 state-of-the-art cryptography. It aims to be faster, simpler, leaner, and
 more useful than IPSec, while avoiding the massive headache. It intends to
 be considerably more performant than OpenVPN.  WireGuard is designed as a
 general purpose VPN for running on embedded interfaces and super computers
 alike, fit for many different circumstances. It uses UDP.

